subSubSection.paragraph:
The name 
Blechum capense
Burm. f. has been erroneously applied to this new Polynesian species (
Brown and Brown 1931
; 
Copeland 1932
). The true 
Blechnum capense
is confined to southern Africa and some nearby islands (
Burrows 1990
; 
Roux 2001
). This southern African species has also been treated under the name 
Blechnum sylvaticum
Schelpe
(Schelpe 1979; 
Jacobson 1983
), on the false assumption that the type of Blechnum capense Burm. f. was a mixed collection of two species (
Jacobson 1983
). However, there seem to be good reasons for placing 
Blechnum sylvaticum
in synonymy under 
Blechnum capense
(Roux 1982; 
Schelpe and Anthony 1986
; 
Burrows 1990
; 
Roux 2001
).
